Job Application Form Webpage
This project is a simple, yet fully functional job application form created using HTML and CSS. The form is designed to capture 
essential applicant details and provides a user-friendly interface for submitting job applications. 
This repository contains all the necessary files to view and customize the form, including a screenshot of the webpage for reference.

Project Overview
The job application form includes the following sections:

Personal Information: Fields for name, email, phone number, and address.
Position Details: Drop-down menus and text fields to specify the position applied for, desired salary, and start date.
Education and Experience: Text areas for educational background, work experience, and skills.
Attachments: Option to upload a resume and cover letter.
Submission: A submit button to send the application.

Files in This Repository
index.html: The HTML file containing the structure of the job application form.
styles.css: The CSS file for styling the form, ensuring it is visually appealing and responsive.
screenshot.png: A screenshot of the job application form webpage, showcasing the final design.

Features
Responsive Design: The form layout adjusts to different screen sizes, making it accessible on both desktop and mobile devices.
User-Friendly Interface: Clear labels and organized sections guide applicants through the form, making the application process straightforward.
Customizable: The HTML and CSS code can be easily modified to fit different design preferences and additional form fields can be added as needed.

